  "text": "Memory pressure pod eviction in Kubernetes is implemented through a multi-component system defined in the kubelet eviction package. Here are the key findings:\n\n**Eviction Threshold Definition:**\nThe memory pressure eviction thresholds are defined in `pkg/kubelet/eviction/api/types.go` through two signals:\n- `SignalMemoryAvailable` (signal: \"memory.available\") - measures memory available for allocation\n- `SignalAllocatableMemoryAvailable` (signal: \"allocatableMemory.available\") - measures allocatable memory remaining\n\nThe default hard eviction threshold for memory pressure is defined in `pkg/kubelet/eviction/defaults_linux.go` as `DefaultEvictionHard[\"memory.available\"] = \"100Mi\"`. This means eviction is triggered when available memory drops below 100 MiB.\n\n**Eviction Manager Implementation:**\nThe core eviction logic is implemented in `pkg/kubelet/eviction/eviction_manager.go` through the `managerImpl` type:\n- `NewManager()` creates the eviction manager with configured thresholds\n- `Start()` initiates the monitoring control loop and memory threshold notifiers\n- `synchronize()` is the main control loop that:\n  1. Collects resource usage observations via `makeSignalObservations()`\n  2. Evaluates thresholds against observations using `thresholdsMet()`\n  3. Maps thresholds to node conditions (NodeMemoryPressure) via the helpers\n  4. Ranks pods for eviction using `rankMemoryPressure()` when memory signals exceed thresholds\n  5. Terminates selected pods via `evictPod()`\n\n**Decision Logic in `pkg/kubelet/eviction/helpers.go`:**\n- `thresholdsMet()` determines if available memory is less than the threshold using LessThan operator comparison\n- `nodeConditions()` maps memory signals to `v1.NodeMemoryPressure` condition via `signalToNodeCondition` map\n- `rankMemoryPressure()` sorts pods for eviction considering:\n  - Pods exceeding memory requests (via `exceedMemoryRequests()`)\n  - QoS priority (via `priority()`)\n  - Actual memory usage (via `memory()`)\n\n**Threshold Parsing and Configuration:**\n- `ParseThresholdConfig()` in helpers.go parses kubelet configuration flags (EvictionHard, EvictionSoft, etc.)\n- The KubeletConfiguration fields in `pkg/kubelet/apis/config/types.go` define the eviction parameters\n- Configuration is initiated in `pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go` when creating the eviction manager\n\n**Memory Threshold Notifications:**\n- On Linux with cgroup v1, `pkg/kubelet/eviction/threshold_notifier_linux.go` implements kernel-level memory threshold notifications via eventfd and epoll\n- Enables immediate eviction response when memory thresholds are crossed"
}

